Exercise: Contralateral Superman
Utility: Auxiliary
Mechanics: Isolated
Force: Pull
Preparation: Lie prone on mat with legs together and arms extended out on floor approximately parallel.
Execution: Raise left arm and shoulder and right leg up off floor. Lower arm and shoulder and leg to floor. Repeat by raising and lowering right arm and shoulder and left leg. Repeat by alternating between opposite sides.
Comments: Lift legs and arms deliberately with no jerking. Also see bilateral movement: Superman.
Target: Erector Spinae
Synergists: Gluteus Maximus, Hamstrings, Trapezius, Lower, Trapezius, Middle
Stabilizers: Deltoid, Anterior, Deltoid, Lateral, Splenius
